# Started by `lwpt init`, extended to the lwpt-ecosystem convention.

# Build artefacts (per the native-nostalgia-stack build-system contract,
# everything output by the build lands under build/ and is not committed).
build/

# LWPT toolkit state — the install workspace, session scratch, and the
# ephemeral install lock. The committed state under .lwpt/modules/ and
# .lwpt/archives/ is NOT gitignored (zero-install, mirroring lwpt's
# ADR-0002): a fresh clone builds with plain fpc, no lwpt required.
.lwpt/tmp/
.lwpt/sessions/
.lwpt/install.lock

# FPC artefacts. These should never appear with -FE build, but defensive
# in case a contributor runs fpc by hand without the output-dir flag.
*.o
*.ppu
*.rsj
*.compiled

# OS noise.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
